      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Negative liberty, as championed by thinkers like Isaiah Berlin, emphasizes freedom *from* external coercion, which is precisely what regulation imposes. When the government mandates rules for online speech, it is actively interfering with the individual's ability to express themselves without state interference. Even regulations aimed at \"safety\" function as a constraint, effectively turning the state into a censor controlling the flow of ideas.",
      "source": "target",
